docs.lead_paragraph: Gov. Gina Raimondo of Rhode Island defeated a liberal challenger in a Democratic primary election on Wednesday, according to The Associated Press, reasserting herself as the party’s leader in a state where she has battled criticism from activists on the left and intransigence from old-guard lawmakers in her own camp.

headline.main: Gina Raimondo, Rhode Island Governor, Turns Back Liberal Challenge in Primary
